text.tspan: C. Measures in the final network
A. Initial network: agents are embedded in different types of networks (small-world, scale-free, cliques)
where different types of network measures are controlled. B. Each round, agents communicate with their neighbors.
step1: agents have a prior distribution of the language features, and they extract an utterance based on this prior distribution (step 2).
Then, they hear their neighbors' utterance and update their posterior distribution.
